LINE.Text: The Beatles released a total of 310 songs as group. Of those 235 were written by one or more Beatle.
This analysis focuses on the time between 1964 and 1970 when the Beatles released 18 albums &
175 songs. Within that span they had 52 top 100 hits in the US and 21 #1 hits. Source: Wikipedia
WHO WROTE MOST of THEIR SONGS?
Lennon, McCartney or some combination wrote 86% of all Beatle's songs.
WHAT ARE MOST of THEIR SONGS ABOUT?
Love is the most common lyric used in all Beatle songs. It was used 312 times in 42% of their songs.
WHICH SONGWRITER HAS the LARGEST VOCABULARY?
Their songs average 65 unique words/song: 33% of songs referencing love were hits rs. 21% without.
